title: Design review..
content:
I'm doing a non-profit job herem I basically just threw this mark together quite quick. Let me know what you guys think, and see if you can guess the type face ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20131018075844im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)   
   
 [http://www.kylehildebrant.com/downloads/fmug\_logo\_comps.pdf](http://web.archive.org/web/20131018075844/http:/www.kylehildebrant.com/downloads/fmug_logo_comps.pdf)
author: Hildebrant

comments.content:
I was so excited about that, being that the bolder weight and the regular weight matched nearly perfectly at that size combination.   
   
On colors, well, maybe not, I can't say its for everyone, but its a combination I have been dying to use on something, and a "free" project seemed the best bet.   
   
Ohh and you don't count for the font guessing ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20131018075844im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif) too good my dear Stephan, just too good. ![:-)](http://web.archive.org/web/20131018075844im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/clipart/happy.gif)

The typeface is Faceplate Sans from [PsyOps](http://web.archive.org/web/20131018075844/http:/www.psyops.com/).   
   
I don't like the color combo, but the caps/lc combo at the   
same weight works well. It's a decent logo, Kyle. Good job.
